cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper deals with the problem of dropped pronouns in machine translation, which is a common issue in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a deep learning-based approach, which suggests that it could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of recurrent neural networks and multilayer perceptrons indicates that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of alignment information and features, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well.
